title: Queen - Oxford, UK - November 20 1973 AUD (Including Soundcheck)
description:
Queen
"New Theatre" Oxford, UK - November 20 1973 AUD

Lineage: Trade CD-R > EAC > WAV > FLAC Level 8 > DIME

Comments from queenconcerts.com: This show is a MUST for every fan. Not only it includes Hangman but it also has a soundcheck
 at the beginning of the CD! It's superb to hear parts of various songs during the soundcheck (e.g. Ogre Battle without Brian
's guitar etc.) Quality is very good minus. I compiled this CD from several bootlegs so you get the best quality available 
(Supporting Mott The Hoople bootleg has worse quality than most of this).

   1. Soundcheck: Guitar Intro/Ogre Battle/Procession/Father to Son/Procession/Son and Daughter/Guitar Bits/
                  Bama Lama Bamma Loo/Keep Yourself Alive
   2. Procession
   3. Father to Son
   4. Son and Daughter
   5. Ogre Battle
   6. Hangman
   7. Keep Yourself Alive
   8. Liar
   9. Jailhouse Rock
  10. Shake, Rattle & Roll
  11. Stupid Cupid
  12. Be Bop A Lula
  13. Jailhouse Rock reprise
  14. Bama Lama Bamma Loo 

Length: 63 min
Line up: Freddie Mercury, Brian May, John Deacon, Roger Taylor.
